In order to demonstrate the usefulness of our model in enhancing transportation efficiency, we use our new calibrated model to tackle the bottleneck flow with a prescribed social distance. Bottlenecks are usually due to a narrow section of road, a junction, or a door that impedes pedestrian flow. To study the bottleneck motion base case, we specifically simulate people exiting a square room of 20 m by 20 m via a door located in the middle of the right wall, which is illustrated in Fig. 2a. The width of the door is chosen to be 36 in. (0.92 m), which is a common door width in the U.S. The simulation starts with 60 individuals with random initial locations, directions, and identical velocity magnitude of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
